        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> President Zelenskyy
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-signed-a-bill?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >signed a bill</a
            >
            that reduces the independence of two key anti-corruption agencies by
            placing them under the control of the prosecutor general. This will
            erase Russian influence from the system and reopen stalled criminal
            cases involving key officials. However, critics warn that the bill
            can undermine Ukraine‚Äôs EU integration and make the anti-corruption
            bodies dependent institutions.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
